➜“雾霾”的英语是“haze”、“fog”还是“smog”呢？
http://www.sohu.com/a/432574882_115013	5992
<p>入冬以后，</p>
<p>蓝天白云渐行渐远，</p>
<p>北京及大部分北方城市又陷入了四面“霾”伏。</p>
<p>这期我们就来聊聊“雾霾”相关的英语。</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p6.itc.cn/images01/20201118/6d3e530b7f4a4b38b11c018cfadcdc44.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p>这里我们需要辨析的有五个词：</p>
<p>Mist, Fog, Smog, Haze 和Vog</p>
<p>Mist and fog are caused by water droplets in the air, and the only difference is how far you can see. The condition is called being foggy if you are not being able to see more than 1,000 meters in terms of airline industry and more than 200 meters in terms of civilian. If you can see further than that, it is mist.</p>
<p>Mist和fog是由空气中的小水滴造成的，它们俩区分的条件是你能看清楚的距离有多远。如果你看不到超过1000米的航空视野范围，看不到超过200米的城市视野范围，这种情况被称为fog。如果您能看到的视野范围更多，那就是mist(薄雾)。</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p0.itc.cn/images01/20201118/fc066bf85a3b45fe80a5160a8eabe494.png" max-width="600" /></p>            <div class="lookall-box">
<div class="lookall-shadow"></div>
